---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy" noindex={true}>
  <div class="container legal-page">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 26, 2026</p>

    <h2>What cookies are</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small text files stored in your browser when you visit a website. They are used to remember preferences and improve experience.</p>

    <h2>Cookies we use</h2>

    <h3>Necessary cookies</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>cookie-consent:</strong> Stores your cookie preference. Duration: 1 year. Stored locally (localStorage).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Advertising cookies (require consent)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google AdSense:</strong> Cookies used to show personalized ads. Only activated if you accept cookies. Provider: Google Ireland Limited. More info: <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google ads policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to manage cookies</h2>
    <p>You can accept or reject cookies via the banner that appears on your first visit. You can also configure your browser:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings > Privacy and security > Cookies</li>
      <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options > Privacy and security</li>
      <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences > Privacy</li>
      <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings > Cookies and permissions</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Change your preference</h2>
    <p>To change your cookie preference, clear site data in your browser and reload the page. The consent banner will appear again.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-page h1 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal-page h2 { margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .legal-page h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .legal-page p, .legal-page li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal-page ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
</style>
